# =============================================================================
# Multi-Chain Crypto Wallet - .gitignore
# =============================================================================
# This file prevents sensitive data, build artifacts, and unnecessary files
# from being committed to version control.

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY-CRITICAL: NEVER COMMIT THESE FILES
# =============================================================================

# Private Keys and Wallets (CRITICAL - Never commit these!)
*.wallet
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*private_key*
*private-key*
*privatekey*
wallet.json
keystore/
keys/
wallets/
.wallet/

# Mnemonic Phrases and Seeds (CRITICAL - Never commit these!)
*mnemonic*
*seed*
*recovery*
*backup*
seed.txt
mnemonic.txt
recovery.txt
backup.txt

# Environment Files with Secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.test
.env.production
.env.staging
*.env

# Configuration files that might contain secrets
config.json
secrets.json
credentials.json
auth.json

# =============================================================================
# RUST BUILD ARTIFACTS
# =============================================================================

# Cargo build outputs
/target/
/backend/target/
/frontend/target/
**/target/

# Cargo lock file (include for applications, exclude for libraries)
# Since this is a wallet application (not a library), we'll keep Cargo.lock
# Cargo.lock

# Rust compilation cache
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# =============================================================================
# NODE.JS / FRONTEND (Future)
# =============================================================================

# Node modules
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Next.js build output (when we add frontend)
.next/
out/
.vercel/

# Environment variables
.env*.local

# Package manager lock files (keep for reproducible builds)
# package-lock.json
# yarn.lock
# pnpm-lock.yaml

# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT TOOLS
# =============================================================================

# IDE and Editor files
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json
.vscode/extensions.json
.vscode/c_cpp_properties.json
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp
temp/
tmp/

# Log files
*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# =============================================================================
# TESTING AND DEVELOPMENT DATA
# =============================================================================

# Test databases and data
test.db
test.sqlite
*.db-journal
db.sqlite*

# Coverage reports
coverage/
*.lcov
.nyc_output/

# Benchmark results
benchmark-results/
*.bench

# =============================================================================
# OPERATING SYSTEM FILES
# =============================================================================

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
.VolumeIcon.icns
.com.apple.timemachine.donotpresent
.fseventsd
.DocumentRevisions-V100
.TemporaryItems
.apdisk

# Windows
Thumbs.db
Thumbs.db:encryptable
ehthumbs.db
ehthumbs_vista.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/
*.cab
*.msi
*.msix
*.msm
*.msp
*.lnk

# Linux
*~
.fuse_hidden*
.directory
.Trash-*
.nfs*

# =============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION AND GENERATED FILES
# =============================================================================

# Documentation build outputs (keep source .md files)
/target/doc/
docs/build/
site/

# Generated documentation
book/
mdbook/
target/doc/

# =============================================================================
# BLOCKCHAIN AND CRYPTO SPECIFIC
# =============================================================================

# Local blockchain data
blockchain/
chain-data/
geth/
.ethereum/

# Local testnet data
testnet/
devnet/
localnet/

# RPC and node data
node_modules/
.ganache/
ganache-cli/

# Transaction receipts and local cache
receipts/
.cache/
cache/

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY TOOLS AND AUDITS
# =============================================================================

# Security audit reports (may contain sensitive info)
audit-reports/
security-reports/
*.audit
vulnerability-report.*

# Static analysis outputs
.clippy_cache/
target/clippy/

# =============================================================================
# BACKUP AND ARCHIVE FILES
# =============================================================================

# Archives
*.zip
*.tar.gz
*.tar
*.rar
*.7z

# Backup files
*.bak
*.backup
*.old
*_backup
*_old

# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLE AND IGNORE PATTERNS FOR FUTURE USE
# =============================================================================

# Example configurations (uncomment if created)
# config.example.json
# .env.example

# Future integration files (uncomment if added)
# docker-compose.override.yml
# .dockerignore

# Database files (uncomment if using local DBs)
# *.sqlite
# *.sqlite3
# *.db

# =============================================================================
# WHITELIST IMPORTANT FILES (Override above patterns)
# =============================================================================

# Force include important files that might be caught by patterns above
# Use ! to override exclusions

# Include example/template files
!.env.example
!config.example.json
!wallet.example.json

# Include documentation
!README.md
!SECURITY.md
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!*.md

# Include important configuration files
!Cargo.toml
!package.json
!tsconfig.json

# Include implementation logs
!implementation-logs/
!implementation-logs/*.md

# =============================================================================
# NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS
# =============================================================================

# This .gitignore is designed specifically for a crypto wallet project.
# Key security considerations:
# 1. Never commit private keys, mnemonics, or seeds
# 2. Never commit environment files with API keys or secrets
# 3. Be extra cautious with any file that might contain sensitive data
# 4. Review all commits to ensure no secrets are accidentally included
# 5. Use tools like git-secrets or gitleaks for additional protection
#
# For sensitive development:
# 1. Use separate .env files for different environments
# 2. Store test mnemonics/keys separately from production
# 3. Use hardware wallets for any real funds during development
# 4. Regularly audit dependencies for security vulnerabilities
#
# Remember: Once committed to git, files can be difficult to completely remove
# from git history. Prevention is better than remediation.